{
  "texts": [
    "The limited genomic variable scope in EHRs incurs an exceedingly small a priori probability for discovery, and these two factors together, further exacerbate the low power issue.",
    "Newer Big Science designs e.g., VA's MVP project [62] or the AllOfUs project [63] are poised to overcome these difficulties.",
    "Powersample design, is harder in ML because knowledge of learning curves is required but often only empirically known (see Chapter \"The Development Process and Lifecycle of Clinical Grade and Other Safety and Performance-Sensitive AI/ML Models\" for guidance).",
    "In some cases assumption-driven and early data-fitted empirical learning curves failed to produce unbiased estimates (as for example occured in [64]).",
    "Causality in Early and Modern MLOne of the most foundational aspects of AI/ML for improving health outcomes and the healthcare system and for driving advances in health science discovery is causality, its discovery, representation, and modeling."
  ]
}